rise Program The mission statement of Virginia Military Institute defines our purpose to train cadets to become  advocates of the American Democracy and free enterprise system  The John W  and Jane M  Roberts American Free Enterprise Program has been an essential component in achieving this mission  Established in the department of economics and business in 1998  the program is made possible by the generosity and support of Mr  and Mrs  John Roberts  founders of the Solite Corporation  It is a demonstrated historical fact that free markets have created higher standards of living for the greatest number of people than any other economic system yet devised  We believe that it is in the national interest that the citizenry be imbued with an understanding of the importance of maintaining and defending the role of free markets in our American way of life  The Roberts Fund has been instrumental in supporting the department and its unique degree program that combines the conceptual framework of an economics degree with the business applications that are common to a degree in business administration  With an economics and business faculty that has a bent toward teaching free market economics and business applications  we are among the few colleges and universities that have the free enterprise system at its central core  One of the main purposes of the Roberts Fund was to support the department in gaining wider recognition for the work we do  Because of the support of Mr  and Mrs  Roberts  the department is now accredited by AACSB   International  the principle accrediting body for business programs in the world  As a wholly undergraduate program  VMI is among a very select group of schools that have achieved this distinction  The John W  and Jane M  Roberts American Free Enterprise Program is made possible because of the unswerving support of Mr  and Mrs  Roberts  founders of the Solite Corporation  Established in the department in 1998  the program supports  2 Institute Professorships The John W  and Jane M  Roberts Institute Professorship in Free Enterprise Economics The John W  and Jane M  Roberts Institute Professorship in Free Enterprise Business The John W  and Jane M  Roberts Lecture Series Departmental Internships Funds for Faculty and Cadet Research Resources for Departmental Awards In recognition of the important role that Mr  and Mrs  Roberts have played in our department  our highest award for cadet achievement  the Roberts Medal Academic Achievement Award is presented each year to the top ranking cadet in the graduating class  The award consists of a medal and a cash prize  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu Virginia Military Institute   Roberts  American Free Enterprise Program  skip to content VMI VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI Menu About About Us Administrative Offices Institute Report News  Photos  Videos VMI Archives Museums VMI Museum System The VMI Museum New Market Battlefield Stonewall Jackson House For Visitors Directions   Map Employment Parents   Family Conferences Chessie Nature Trail Bookstore Resources MyVMI Directories Friendly URLs Post View Health and Safety Computing Academics Areas of Study Majors   Minors Arts   Humanities Engineering Information   Social Sciences Life Sciences Natural Sciences ROTC Enrichment Institute Honors Program International Programs Service Opportunities Summer Programs Institute Writing Program Research Support Cadet Counseling Career Services Disabilities Services Miller Academic Center Advising Math Resource Center The Writing Center Resources Registrar Financial Aid Canvas Login Dean s Office Career Services Bookstore Cadet Computing Admissions Corps Life Athletics Library   Archives Preston Library Library Home Find Books Departments Media Equipment Technical Services Visitor Information Archives Archives Home Online Exhibits VMI History FAQs Genealogy   Alumni Manuscripts Civil War   New Market Give Close Menu Information   Social Sciences Economics   Business Home Degrees   Programs Courses Economics Newsletter Departmental Activities Awards Cadet Investment Group EC BU Internship Program McDowell Scholarship Free Enterprise Program Beta Gamma Sigma Omicron Delta Epsilon BRIDGE VMI Service Club Policies   Forms About ECBU Faculty Open House Presentation Senior Exit Survey Alumni  97    07 survey Donna Potter Executive Secretary P   540  464 7234 F   540  464 7005 Virginia Military Institute 345 Scott Shipp Hall Lexington  VA  24450 Contact ECBU Home   Academics   Areas of Study   Social Science   Economics   Business   Roberts  American Free Enterprise Program Roberts American Free Enterprise Program The mission statement of Virginia Military Institute defines our purpose to train cadets to become  advocates of the American Democracy and free enterprise system  The John W  and Jane M  Roberts American Free Enterprise Program has been an essential component in achieving this mission  Established in the department of economics and business in 1998  the program is made possible by the generosity and support of Mr  and Mrs  John Roberts  founders of the Solite Corporation  It is a demonstrated historical fact that free markets have created higher standards of living for the greatest number of people than any other economic system yet devised  We believe that it is in the national interest that the citizenry be imbued with an understanding of the importance of maintaining and defending the role of free markets in our American way of life  The Roberts Fund has been instrumental in supporting the department and its unique degree program that combines the conceptual framework of an economics degree with the business applications that are common to a degree in business administration  With an economics and business faculty that has a bent toward teaching free market economics and business applications  we are among the few colleges and universities that have the free enterprise system at its central core  One of the main purposes of the Roberts Fund was to support the department in gaining wider recognition for the work we do  Because of the support of Mr  and Mrs  Roberts  the department is now accredited by AACSB   International  the principle accrediting body for business programs in the world  As a wholly undergraduate program  VMI is among a very select group of schools that have achieved this distinction  The John W  and Jane M  Roberts American Free Enterprise Program is made possible because of the unswerving support of Mr  and Mrs  Roberts  founders of the Solite Corporation  Established in the department in 1998  the program supports  2 Institute Professorships The John W  and Jane M  Roberts Institute Professorship in Free Enterprise Economics The John W  and Jane M  Roberts Institute Professorship in Free Enterprise Business The John W  and Jane M  Roberts Lecture Series Departmental Internships Funds for Faculty and Cadet Research Resources for Departmental Awards In recognition of the important role that Mr  and Mrs  Roberts have played in our department  our highest award for cadet achievement  the Roberts Medal Academic Achievement Award is presented each year to the top ranking cadet in the graduating class  The award consists of a medal and a cash prize  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadet